02:19.886 --> 02:22.821
It's only been wine
since last July.

02:22.823 --> 02:24.773
Hey, hey, that got
a three-star rating

02:24.775 --> 02:26.391
in the Wal-Mart wine tracker.

02:26.393 --> 02:28.310
What's the big deal?

02:28.312 --> 02:30.445
So, I need a few glasses
to loosen me up.

02:30.447 --> 02:31.830
Are you saying you
need to get loaded

02:31.832 --> 02:32.914
in order to have sex with me?

02:32.916 --> 02:35.283
I'm not loaded.
Fine.

02:35.285 --> 02:37.352
But it doesn't hurt.

02:38.454 --> 02:40.121
Hey, guys.

02:40.123 --> 02:42.073
Wally! Want some wine?

02:42.075 --> 02:44.459
No, I don't like to drink
when I'm depressed.

02:44.461 --> 02:46.261
Wally, it's the best time
to drink.

02:46.263 --> 02:49.264
Also when you're bored, lonely,
or just, you know,

02:49.266 --> 02:50.565
too sober.

02:51.417 --> 02:52.884
Why are you depressed?

02:52.886 --> 02:54.135
I don't know.

02:54.137 --> 02:55.470
It's kind of personal.

02:55.472 --> 02:57.689
Okay, no problem.

02:59.058 --> 03:00.275
What do you do when you

03:00.277 --> 03:02.193
tell someone you love them
and they don't respond?

03:02.195 --> 03:04.946
Drink.

03:04.948 --> 03:06.898
Wait, you told Zoey
you love her?

03:06.900 --> 03:08.483
Yeah, I thought the plane
was gonna crash,

03:08.485 --> 03:09.818
and it just kind of came out,

03:09.820 --> 03:12.671
along with a little squirt
of pee.

03:13.489 --> 03:15.540
So, what did she say?

03:15.542 --> 03:19.944
"Oh, God,
oh, God, I don't want to die."

03:19.946 --> 03:22.964
Well, given the circumstance,
that's a legitimate response.

03:22.966 --> 03:24.082
Sure, in the moment,

03:24.084 --> 03:25.634
but what about
after the plane leveled out?

03:25.636 --> 03:26.584
Well, what did she say then?

03:26.586 --> 03:29.421
"Why do I smell pee?"

03:32.558 --> 03:34.426
Then we just sat there
in silence

03:34.428 --> 03:36.094
for the rest of the flight.

03:36.096 --> 03:38.113
Should have drank.

03:39.965 --> 03:42.767
Yeah, well, I'm gonna go
change my underwear

03:42.769 --> 03:44.185
before I get diaper rash.

03:45.971 --> 03:48.323
Wow, I feel bad for him.

03:48.325 --> 03:49.741
Yeah.

03:49.743 --> 03:51.809
I mean, you know, to tell
somebody you love them,

03:51.811 --> 03:54.079
and just get no response.

03:54.081 --> 03:56.097
Awful.

03:59.151 --> 04:00.852
You know how I feel
about you, right?

04:00.854 --> 04:01.986
Right.

04:01.988 --> 04:03.705
You know how I
feel about you.

04:03.707 --> 04:06.708
Oh, absolutely.

04:09.962 --> 04:12.030
Still nice to hear
on occasion.

04:12.032 --> 04:14.182
Oh, I agree.

04:17.153 --> 04:21.272
I can do this
as long as you can, pal.

04:26.396 --> 04:27.729
It's open.

04:27.731 --> 04:29.447
Hey.

04:29.449 --> 04:30.782
Can I talk to you for a minute?

04:30.784 --> 04:32.067
Sure. What's up?

04:33.686 --> 04:35.870
I didn't sleep at all
last night, man.

04:35.872 --> 04:37.856
This Zoey stuff
is making me crazy.

04:37.858 --> 04:39.357
Oh, man, I'm sorry.

04:39.359 --> 04:41.793
I'm starting to wonder

04:41.795 --> 04:44.379
if I should break
up with her,

04:44.381 --> 04:46.364
Oh, hang on. I mean,
just because she didn't say,

04:46.366 --> 04:48.299
"I love you," doesn't mean
she doesn't feel it.

04:48.301 --> 04:49.634
You think?

04:49.636 --> 04:51.536
Oh, yeah, yeah.
Some people have a hard time

04:51.538 --> 04:52.504
articulating their feelings,

04:52.506 --> 04:54.756
so they express them
in other ways.

04:59.128 --> 05:00.044
Is that Lyndsey?

05:01.181 --> 05:03.765
Yeah, she had a little
too much vino last night.

05:03.767 --> 05:06.768
Anyway, I think you just have
to be patient with Zoey.

05:08.905 --> 05:11.222
Yeah, I guess.

05:15.411 --> 05:18.729
Sorry, I... I have a...
a hard time with...

05:18.731 --> 05:20.582
people throwing up.

05:20.584 --> 05:23.251
Try watching
and holding her hair.

05:23.253 --> 05:26.404
It's just, Zoey's going
to England for a few weeks.

05:29.842 --> 05:31.426
And-and I'm th...

05:32.628 --> 05:34.763
I'm-I'm starting to
think if...

05:34.765 --> 05:37.582
if I'm gonna end it,
now would be a good time.

05:37.584 --> 05:39.768
Well, it...

05:42.388 --> 05:43.688
Whoa.

05:43.690 --> 05:45.607
You think I'd be
used to it by now.

05:45.609 --> 05:47.258
No, no, no, don't...

05:47.260 --> 05:48.526
Don't do anything hasty.

05:51.814 --> 05:54.816
I can't... I... I can't
just leave th...

05:54.818 --> 05:57.318
I can't just leave things
the way that they are.

05:57.320 --> 06:00.038
Why don't you...
Why don't you go talk to her,

06:00.040 --> 06:03.041
you know, and just put
your caaards on the table.

06:05.110 --> 06:07.045
Yeah, maybe.

06:07.047 --> 06:08.446
Crap,

06:08.448 --> 06:10.482
now I've got to change my bra.

06:13.586 --> 06:16.221
I-I-I mean, maybe we should
just give her some privacy.

06:16.223 --> 06:20.775
Oh, God,
now it's coming out both ends!

06:20.777 --> 06:23.061
Good idea.

06:27.850 --> 06:29.767
Ava, you need
to get dressed.

06:29.769 --> 06:31.936
Mummy has to go.

06:34.156 --> 06:35.523
Walden.

06:35.525 --> 06:36.941
De-e-lightful.

06:36.943 --> 06:40.912
Nigel, di-isgusting.

06:42.915 --> 06:44.482
What, are you here
to pick up your daughter?

06:44.484 --> 06:45.834
I am.

06:45.836 --> 06:48.203
Zoey tell you that we took
my jet to San Francisco

06:48.205 --> 06:50.038
last night for fried clams?

06:50.040 --> 06:52.674
No, she did not.

06:52.676 --> 06:54.926
Well, we did.

06:54.928 --> 06:57.595
Are you sharing this information
just to upset me?

06:57.597 --> 07:01.499
Actually, I was hoping to make
you feel inadequate as well.

07:01.501 --> 07:02.600
Oh, Walden.

07:02.602 --> 07:04.035
What are you
doing here?

07:04.037 --> 07:05.436
Nigel, I'm running late,

07:05.438 --> 07:07.138
so will you for once please
make yourself useful

07:07.140 --> 07:08.356
and help Ava get ready?

07:08.358 --> 07:11.359
Well, only because
you asked so nicely.

07:11.361 --> 07:12.694
Enjoy her.

07:12.696 --> 07:13.978
Hi.

07:13.980 --> 07:15.029
We need to talk.

07:15.031 --> 07:17.115
Now? I'm about to leave
for the airport.

07:17.117 --> 07:18.149
I'll take you.

07:18.151 --> 07:19.951
Thanks, but I have a car coming.

07:19.953 --> 07:21.202
Now, where is my passport?

07:21.204 --> 07:22.787
Nigel, have you
seen my passport?

07:22.789 --> 07:24.072
I don't live
here, Zoey,

07:24.074 --> 07:26.040
I merely
pay the rent.

07:26.042 --> 07:28.126
Look, I just don't want
to leave things between us

07:28.128 --> 07:29.210
the way that they are.

07:29.212 --> 07:30.161
Everything's fine.

07:30.163 --> 07:31.379
No, it's not.

07:31.381 --> 07:32.863
I said I love you,
and the only thing

07:32.865 --> 07:35.750
I got in response is the not
very surprising information

07:35.752 --> 07:37.868
that you don't want to die
in a crashing plane.

07:37.870 --> 07:39.804
Can't we discuss this
when I get back?

07:39.806 --> 07:40.755
What's there to discuss?

07:40.757 --> 07:43.708
You either love me,
or you don't.

07:43.710 --> 07:46.561
Walden, I'm about to leave
on an important business trip,

07:46.563 --> 07:48.963
and the last thing I need
right now is more pressure.

07:48.965 --> 07:50.181
I'm not pressuring you.

07:50.183 --> 07:52.216
I'm just asking you for a
simple, definitive answer

07:52.218 --> 07:53.601
right now before you leave.

07:53.603 --> 07:55.353
What was that?

07:55.355 --> 07:57.888
Sorry, just knocked over
your Chinese table lamp.

07:57.890 --> 07:59.290
Perhaps you can
buy another one

07:59.292 --> 08:01.609
next time you jet
to Francisco.

08:03.162 --> 08:04.562
It came up.

08:04.564 --> 08:08.116
I'm sorry, I just don't have
the time for this now, okay?

08:08.118 --> 08:10.084
Ava, are you dressed?

08:11.870 --> 08:14.839
That seems pretty
definitive to me.

08:17.576 --> 08:18.743
That's it.

08:18.745 --> 08:20.795
No more relationships.
I'm done.

08:20.797 --> 08:22.130
Finished; just over.

08:27.803 --> 08:29.137
Hi.

08:29.139 --> 08:31.022
Hi.

08:33.859 --> 08:35.393
And I'm back.

