Who had corn chowder
for dinner last night?

09:07.124 --> 09:09.391
How do you know anybody
had corn chowder last night?

09:09.393 --> 09:11.480
'Cause it's dripping
all over your bathroom.

09:11.505 --> 09:12.705
Oh.

09:12.963 --> 09:14.012
Sorry about that.

09:14.014 --> 09:16.465
Uh, Lyndsey got a little bit...

09:16.467 --> 09:18.067
queasy this morning.

09:18.069 --> 09:19.151
Is she pregnant?

09:19.153 --> 09:21.353
Oh, no, no, gosh, no.

09:22.773 --> 09:24.473
Absolutely not.

09:25.859 --> 09:27.693
Here.

09:27.695 --> 09:28.777
Me?

09:28.779 --> 09:30.529
Not my girlfriend,
not my vomit,

09:30.531 --> 09:31.997
not my problem.

09:33.333 --> 09:34.333
I'll clean it up.

09:34.335 --> 09:35.150
You will?

09:35.152 --> 09:36.585
For 75 bucks.

09:36.587 --> 09:38.370
That's great.

09:38.372 --> 09:40.706
Hey, everybody.

09:42.658 --> 09:44.710
This is Jennifer.
Hi.

09:45.495 --> 09:47.513
- Hey.
- Hey.

09:48.548 --> 09:50.265
Well, let's go take
a walk on the beach.

09:50.267 --> 09:51.383
Great.

09:51.385 --> 09:52.501
Uh, Walden,
before you go,

09:52.503 --> 09:55.053
can I talk to you
for a minute?

09:59.726 --> 10:01.009
I'll bring him right back.

10:01.011 --> 10:02.444
You'd better.

10:05.648 --> 10:06.848
My name's Jake.

10:06.850 --> 10:08.367
Hi, Jake.

10:08.369 --> 10:11.870
My friends call me... Jake.

10:14.207 --> 10:15.574
What are you doing?

10:15.576 --> 10:16.875
Zoey made it perfectly clear.

10:16.877 --> 10:18.494
She doesn't love me or need me.

10:18.496 --> 10:19.878
So, I'm moving on.

10:19.880 --> 10:22.197
You left here an hour ago.

10:22.199 --> 10:24.049
How did you find
another girl already?

10:24.051 --> 10:25.534
Oh, I met her in the elevator.

10:25.536 --> 10:26.885
I've been in
a million elevators.

10:26.887 --> 10:29.338
I never once walked out
with a girl like that.

10:29.340 --> 10:31.256
Maybe you need to work
on your attitude.

10:31.258 --> 10:34.059
What exactly did Zoey say?

10:34.061 --> 10:35.561
No, it's what she <i>didn't</i> say.

10:35.563 --> 10:37.262
She didn't say, "I love you."

10:37.264 --> 10:40.349
Oh, please! If I insisted on
women saying "I love you""

10:40.351 --> 10:43.535
I'd have never have had a
girlfriend, a wife or a mother.

10:46.990 --> 10:49.575
Oh. It's Zoey.

10:51.861 --> 10:53.895
Hello?

10:53.897 --> 10:56.398
So, Jennifer,
how old are you?

10:56.400 --> 10:58.200
24. How old are you?

10:58.202 --> 11:00.285
I'm... 24-and-a-half.

11:00.287 --> 11:02.404
Hmm.

11:07.594 --> 11:09.761
Hmm?

11:10.547 --> 11:12.381
I'm surprised
that you called.

11:12.383 --> 11:13.599
Where are you?

11:13.601 --> 11:14.933
On the plane.

11:14.935 --> 11:16.051
We're sitting at the gate.

11:16.053 --> 11:17.636
- Are you okay?
- No.

11:17.638 --> 11:20.138
I feel miserable
about the way we left things.

11:20.140 --> 11:22.140
- You do?
- Yeah.

11:22.142 --> 11:24.259
I've just been so stressed
and busy lately

11:24.261 --> 11:26.395
that I haven't been able
to think straight.

11:26.397 --> 11:29.431
But sitting here
for the last 40 minutes

11:29.433 --> 11:33.268
without so much
as a bloody glass of water,

11:33.270 --> 11:35.604
I've come to a realization.

11:35.606 --> 11:37.039
I'm listening.

11:37.041 --> 11:39.124
The reason I haven't said...

11:39.126 --> 11:41.126
those words to you

11:41.128 --> 11:43.078
is because I'm afraid

11:43.080 --> 11:46.381
that if I do say them,
something bad will happen.

11:46.383 --> 11:47.833
Why would you think that?

11:47.835 --> 11:49.718
'Cause it always has.

11:49.720 --> 11:51.637
I've only said
those words twice.

11:51.639 --> 11:53.788
The last time,
I ended up married

11:53.790 --> 11:56.975
to an insufferable twit.

11:56.977 --> 11:58.126
And the time before that?

11:58.128 --> 11:59.695
I got a thank-you note

11:59.697 --> 12:02.764
and a Swatch watch
from Russell Brand.

12:02.766 --> 12:04.399
Russell Brand?

12:04.401 --> 12:07.152
Mm, not my proudest moment.

12:07.154 --> 12:08.654
Okay. I get it.

12:08.656 --> 12:10.138
So, you're just superstitious
about saying it,

12:10.140 --> 12:13.191
but it has nothing to do with
the way that you feel about me?

12:13.193 --> 12:15.777
No. Not at all.

12:15.779 --> 12:18.146
In fact, the whole reason
I called is

12:18.148 --> 12:19.748
to tell you that I honestly
I...

12:19.750 --> 12:21.250
Oh, there you are.

12:21.252 --> 12:24.953
Ooh! Cool bedroom.

12:24.955 --> 12:25.837
Who's that?

12:25.839 --> 12:29.007
Uh... Berta.

12:29.009 --> 12:31.843
You couldn't even wait
till my plane takes off?!

12:31.845 --> 12:33.962
No, no, Zoey, it's not what you think!
Oh, good-bye, Walden.

12:33.964 --> 12:36.298
Zoey, just...

12:37.600 --> 12:40.185
♪ Awkward!

12:49.512 --> 12:53.448
Oh... I can't believe I kissed
the mouth that did this.

12:54.984 --> 12:57.686
Alan, I need to
talk to you. Oh!

12:59.038 --> 13:00.689
Can we do it out here?

13:00.691 --> 13:02.291
Gladly.

13:02.293 --> 13:03.709
Oh, good Lord!

13:03.711 --> 13:06.712
Looks like someone
cleaned a deer in the bathtub.

13:09.048 --> 13:10.248
What's going on?

13:10.250 --> 13:11.700
Zoey FaceTimed me
from the plane

13:11.702 --> 13:13.218
to tell me that she loves me.

13:13.220 --> 13:13.740
Good.

13:13.765 --> 13:15.295
But she saw Jennifer
in my bedroom.

13:15.296 --> 13:15.976
Bad.

13:16.001 --> 13:17.836
So, naturally, I immediately
tried to call her back.

13:17.841 --> 13:19.341
Good.
But she wouldn't answer.

13:19.343 --> 13:20.759
Bad.
So I'm gonna fuel up my jet,

13:20.761 --> 13:22.227
and fly to London
and beg for forgiveness.

13:22.229 --> 13:24.730
Good.
Will you stop that, Alan?

13:24.732 --> 13:26.898
I-I need you to come with me.
Me? Why?

13:26.900 --> 13:28.684
Because I might need a witness,
and you can say

13:28.686 --> 13:30.152
that you saw that
nothing happened with Jennifer.

13:30.154 --> 13:31.570
Great. I'm your man.

13:34.240 --> 13:35.907
I am not gonna touch that glove.

13:36.892 --> 13:37.909
Come on.

13:37.911 --> 13:39.161
Oh, uh, wait.

13:39.163 --> 13:40.779
I promised Lyndsey
I'd take her out

13:40.781 --> 13:42.280
to a big, fancy,
romantic dinner tonight.

13:42.282 --> 13:43.415
Bring her.
Really?

13:43.417 --> 13:44.232
Yeah, sure.

13:44.234 --> 13:45.400
Well, I guess a private jet

13:45.402 --> 13:46.501
to London does beat

13:46.503 --> 13:48.453
an 11-year-old Volvo
to the Olive Garden.

13:48.455 --> 13:49.871
I'll-I'll pack a bag.

13:49.873 --> 13:51.006
No, no, no, there's no time.

13:51.008 --> 13:52.374
I'll buy you whatever you need
in London.

13:52.376 --> 13:53.842
You're kidding.
Yeah. Come on.

13:53.844 --> 13:55.844
Hey, if Zoey won't say it,
I will.

13:55.846 --> 13:58.079
I love you, Walden Schmidt.

14:08.091 --> 14:09.691
Thank you, Walden.

14:09.693 --> 14:11.610
This is just incredible.

14:11.612 --> 14:13.228
Glad you like it.
Mm.

14:13.230 --> 14:15.197
What did your son say
when you told him

14:15.199 --> 14:16.448
you were flying
to London tonight?

14:16.450 --> 14:19.384
He told me to bring him back
some English pot.

14:20.820 --> 14:24.039
This is definitely
the way to travel.

14:24.041 --> 14:26.441
No boarding passes,
no airport security,

14:26.443 --> 14:27.743
none of those scanners

14:27.745 --> 14:29.795
that show strangers
the size of your dingle.

14:29.797 --> 14:33.298
Don't you worry about
your dingle, honey.

14:33.300 --> 14:35.751
He's a grower, not a shower.

14:35.753 --> 14:36.951
Yeah, he told me.

14:36.953 --> 14:38.887
He tells everyone.

14:44.877 --> 14:47.212
Can I interest
you in a brewski?

14:48.247 --> 14:49.247
What?

14:49.249 --> 14:50.315
That's Polish for

14:50.317 --> 14:52.601
"Do you want a beer?"

14:52.603 --> 14:54.903
I've traveled
extensively through Asia.

14:56.406 --> 14:58.607
Oh. Thanks.

15:00.643 --> 15:02.994
Are you sure Walden said
he'd be right back?

15:02.996 --> 15:04.496
Forget Walden.

15:04.498 --> 15:06.147
Let's talk about us.

15:06.149 --> 15:07.416
Us?

15:07.418 --> 15:09.468
That's English
for you and me.

15:14.707 --> 15:16.958
♪ Poppin' bottles in the ice

15:16.960 --> 15:18.343
♪ Like a blizzard

15:18.345 --> 15:20.512
♪ When we drunk, we do it right,
gettin' slizzard ♪

15:20.514 --> 15:22.431
♪ Like a G-6, like a G-6...

15:22.433 --> 15:24.182
Uh, honey, honey,
why don't you take your seat

15:24.184 --> 15:25.350
and put your seatbelt on?

15:25.352 --> 15:27.502
Pish, pish, party pooper.

15:27.504 --> 15:32.023
Wally, this is so romantic
what you're doing.

15:32.025 --> 15:35.393
You are flying
across a whole ocean

15:35.395 --> 15:38.063
just to win back
the woman you love.

15:38.065 --> 15:40.315
Thank you.

15:40.317 --> 15:43.618
Alan, sweetie,
I need to tell you something.

15:43.620 --> 15:44.853
Yeah?

15:44.855 --> 15:46.905
I know I give you a hard time,

15:46.907 --> 15:49.574
but in my heart,

15:49.576 --> 15:53.578
I really, really
love...

15:56.250 --> 15:57.466
Oh, God!

15:57.468 --> 15:59.301
Oh. Aah.

15:59.303 --> 16:00.418
I'm so sorry.

16:00.420 --> 16:01.503
Oh! Oh!

16:01.505 --> 16:03.204
Oh. Oh.

16:03.206 --> 16:04.556
So sorry.
Here. Here.

16:04.558 --> 16:05.974
Oh, thank you.

16:08.011 --> 16:09.210
Oh, God!

16:09.212 --> 16:11.213
Oh!
Oh, my God!

16:11.215 --> 16:12.481
Oh, hang on.
Oh, God!

16:12.483 --> 16:14.065
I'll-I'll get...
I'll get some towels.

16:16.219 --> 16:17.652
<i>Okay, folks,</i>

16:17.654 --> 16:19.571
<i>we've got clear skies ahead,</i>

16:19.573 --> 16:22.407
<i>and we'll be in London</i>
<i>in approximately four hours.</i>

16:22.409 --> 16:25.243
<i>So, just sit back and enjoy</i>
<i>the rest of your flight.</i>

16:28.549 --> 16:31.283
♪ Men.

16:31.285 --> 16:33.418
Bottom line, Zoey,
I can assure you

16:33.420 --> 16:36.087
that nothing happened
between Walden and that woman.

16:36.089 --> 16:37.255
Really?

16:37.257 --> 16:39.508
What possible reason
would I have to lie to you?

16:39.510 --> 16:40.742
Well, for one thing, he gave

16:40.744 --> 16:42.577
you and Lyndsey a
free trip to London,

16:42.579 --> 16:44.212
where you all
inexplicably decided

16:44.214 --> 16:46.498
to dress up
like Japanese tourists.

16:47.967 --> 16:49.050
That's my fault.

16:49.052 --> 16:51.102
I kind of threw up
on them a little.

16:51.104 --> 16:53.388
A little?
I might have to get a new plane.

16:53.390 --> 16:56.274
Yes, yes, yes, that's
all very interesting,

16:56.276 --> 16:57.425
but the fact remains

16:57.427 --> 16:59.227
that you still invited
my neighbor Jennifer--

16:59.229 --> 17:00.695
the whore
from the seventh floor--

17:00.697 --> 17:01.813
back to your house.

17:01.815 --> 17:03.565
Yeah, but nothing happened.

17:03.567 --> 17:06.367
Nothing happened 'cause
I called and interrupted you!

17:06.369 --> 17:09.954
Okay, I think we're saying
the same thing here.

17:09.957 --> 17:11.772
Listen, the fact is, I love you.

17:11.775 --> 17:14.376
Okay, and I was an idiot
to put pressure on you,

17:14.377 --> 17:19.181
I made a terrible mistake,
and I'm very, very sorry.

17:24.502 --> 17:27.955
Okay. Uh, we sh...

17:27.958 --> 17:30.091
I think we should go.

17:33.980 --> 17:35.630
I do love you, Walden.

17:37.650 --> 17:39.668
You do?

17:39.670 --> 17:41.653
Of course I do.

17:41.655 --> 17:44.406
That's why I called you
from the plane, you ninny.

17:46.242 --> 17:48.276
So...

17:48.278 --> 17:50.245
you forgive me?

17:50.247 --> 17:51.913
Well, that depends.

17:51.915 --> 17:54.532
Do I have to worry every time
we have a fight

17:54.534 --> 17:57.168
that you're going to go out
and pick up another woman?

17:57.170 --> 18:00.255
Not as long
as I know that you love me.

18:00.257 --> 18:02.424
Good answer.

18:04.176 --> 18:06.327
Come here.

18:17.306 --> 18:19.341
I love you, Lyndsey.

18:19.343 --> 18:22.527
And I love you.

18:24.731 --> 18:26.698
Oh, not in my mouth!

18:26.700 --> 18:28.400
Oh, God.

18:28.402 --> 18:29.868
Oh, dear.

18:44.027 --> 18:46.528
No, seriously, dude. No lie.

18:46.530 --> 18:50.115
All right, fine,
you don't believe me? Here.

18:53.403 --> 18:58.273
Yup. Five times.
Best half hour of my life.

